{center}
{subhead}AmigaDE Player and AmigaDE Shop{def}
{left}
{pp}
Amiga have announced a new product and a new service for users.
{pp}
{bold}AmigaDE Player{nobold}
{pp}
The Player will run on Windows or Linux desktops and allow you to run all
the new AmigaDE applications now available. This will allow the community to
run applications created for Sharp and other Amiga partners.
{pp}
It costs 19.95 (a pre-release offer had it at 14.95 before Sept).
{pp}
Screen shots of the new Player are available on Amiga's website.
Some application due in the near future include: Batty, BoxIkon, Convex,
Lineo and Sol.
{pp}
{bold}AmigaDE Shop{nobold}
{pp}
 The AmigaDE Shop is now open and you can use its service to buy the new
AmigaDE Player.
{pp}
Visit {link http://de.amiga.com/}http://de.amiga.com{end} for more info.
{pp}

